metadata.description: This is a song I wrote about the day I met my wife! I met her at the ashram or monastery I lived in for 8 years. We met at the local grocery store, she walked upto me and gave me a candy from Moscow, where she is from. I still have the wrapper of that candy and it has been 4 and a half years since then. Itâ€™s actually the one on the cover art.

lyrics.text:
Do you remember the day
You walked up to me 
And gave me a candy
Tastes just like honey
Straight out of  moscow
You were wearing golden rays

Faded green birkenstocks, 
White shirt and jeans
Remember the day
as clear as today
as clear as the water

from the oceans and seas

what i felt was as pure
24 carat gold
And I remember the taste 
Tastes just like honey

metadata.name: Tastes like Honey (Acoustic) #1
